    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-19T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-19T05:00:00-05:00" n="93"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/12–1946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Saigon</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saigon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-19T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 19, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 20—3:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>490. Since visit Moffat and <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> correspondents,
                    pro-Vietnam press publishes almost daily critical articles regarding US and its
                    policy, lack of policy, vis-à-vis French-Vietnam dispute—also references to
                    third party intervention with inference that US will eventually seek economic
                    benefits from this dispute. In mentioning tenor of press, long time resident of
                    French Indochina deplores US not taking more positive stand in present dispute
                    and warns failure French-Vietnam negotiations and apparent indifference US can
                    only drive Annamites into Soviet sphere of influence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
